				<text>4.5.4.8 Exercise 8 (Amp Phase x2) (NOT IN QUIZ)</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Given that if \( A\cos\omega t+B\sin\omega t= C\sin (\omega t+\alpha)\)&nbsp; then \[\quad C=\sqrt{A^2+B^2},\qquad \ \cos\alpha=\dfrac{B}{C}, \qquad \sin\alpha=\dfrac{A}{C}.\]</p><p></p><p>Express the following in the amplitude/phase form \(&nbsp;C\sin (\omega t+\alpha). \) Approximate all floating point numbers up to \(4\) d.p.</p>

<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li><p>\(y= {@na3a@}\cos({@na3c@}t)- {@na3b@}\sin({@na3c@}t), \)</p>
<p>\( y = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>

<li><p>\(y= {@na3a@}\cos({@na3c@}t)+ {@na3b@}\sin({@na3c@}t), \)</p>
<p>\( y = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]</p>
</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>Since \[\sin(\omega 
t+\alpha)=\sin\omega t\cos\alpha+\cos\omega t\sin \alpha\] then 
\(A=C\sin\alpha\) (coefficients of \(\cos\omega t\)) and \(B=C\cos\alpha\) 
(coefficients of \(\sin\omega t\),) from which \[C^2=A^2+B^2,\quad  \sin\alpha 
=\dfrac{A}{C},\quad \cos \alpha=\dfrac{B}{C}.\]</p>

<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>
<p>\( C=\sqrt{{@na3a@}^2+ {@na3b@}^2}, \) &nbsp; \( 
\cos\alpha=-\dfrac{{@na3b@}}{{@ta3c@}}\) and \( \sin 
\alpha-\dfrac{{@na3a@}}{{@ta3c@}},\)&nbsp;</p>
<p>so \(\alpha\) is in the second 
quadrant and \(\alpha={@ta3a@}.\)</p>
<p>Therefore \(y={@ta3f@} \).</p>
</li>
<li><p>Similarly, \(y={@ta3f2@} \).</p>
</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
